After getting the new JIRA, Agile plug-in doesn't work and board is unaccessible. Plug-in page reports:
{quote}
This add-on couldn't be loaded. It has one or more errors that prevent it from being enabled
{quote}

As an Administrator, I'd like to add a column showing a different estimation to the plan mode of a board. This would allow administrators to estimate sub-tasks and parents with different Estimation Statistics.
{quote}
We are estimating user stories in story points, and subtasks by hours. When planning for a sprint I see the user stories listed - not the subtasks (which is good and fine), and as I add and remove user stories from the sprint that I am planning, the total number of issues in the sprint updates along with the cumulative story points.

When I officially start a sprint, I can click on any given user story and see the total hours of the subtasks that fall under that story. I need to be able to see that hourly total per user story as I am planning the sprint (before it is committed), so that we can commit to a realistic amount of user stories in the sprint.
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
